review_blob:
Bottled, poured into a pint glass with a pale wheat color. I cant comment on the aroma as my nose is not functioning at the moment.
The flavor actually reminds me of a lager. There is also a hint of fruit flavor and a bit of honey. The aftertaste is flat, perhaps I should call it nonexistent? I would rate Honey Moon a 7 or 8 if only judging macro & mega brews...
beer_name: Blue Moon Honey Moon Summer Ale
